Polonio por correo
Lo lei en <a href="http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=06/11/29/169254"> Polonium-210 Available Through Mail Order</a> y aunque ahora no se lo que dirán al respecto (al principio se decía que el Polonio sólo estaría accesible para servicios secretos y cosas asi), lo cierto es que parece que habría sido posible comprar el tal polonio era posible comprarlo legalmente por internet: <a href="http://www.informationweek.com/internet/showArticle.jhtml?articleID=196513797"> Poison Of Ex-Spy For Sale On The Web</a>.

Por 69 dólares :)

<blockquote>
Polonium-210, which experts say is many times more deadly than cyanide, can be bought legally through United Nuclear Scientific Supplies, a mail-order company that sells through the Web. Chemical companies sell the Polonium-210 legally for industrial use such as removing static electricity from machinery. United Nuclear claims that the material is "currently the only legal Alpha source available without a license."
</blockquote>

La <a href="http://www.unitednuclear.com/">United Nuclear</a> sólo distribuye dentro de los EEUU, y según afirman en su página web en cantidades no peligrosas:

<blockquote>
The amount of Polonium-210, as well as any of the isotopes we sell is an 'exempt quantity' amount. These quantities of radioactive material are not hazardous - this is why they are permitted by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC) to be sold to the general public without any sort of license.
</blockquote>

Y

<blockquote>
You would need about 15,000  of our Polonium-210 needle sources at a total cost of about 1 million - to have a toxic amount.
</blockquote>


